@RogersHistory @TTRadio2021 developed a Covid anxiety disorder in October so have made the decision to leave school-based teaching and go self-employed as an online dyscalculia tutor so I can work from home. Self-care - do something for yourself everyday, even if it's just moisturising.

@RogersHistory @TTRadio2021 Being in the fresh air (although exercise doesn't help my depression, it worsens it). Keeping hobbies going in the good times as well as that keeps your reserves of happiness and fulfillment higher and that helps stave off some anxiety. I have worked part-time for years but...

@RogersHistory @TTRadio2021 and the vagus nerve. I am very open about my depression/anxiety as I feel I've 'pre-warned' them and don't feel so guilty when I'm struggling. Social media has been a great lifeline for me, I get a lot of support from friends in there. Spending time with my bunnies...
